spanGrp.span: ‘There was a man with a rifle;
he dances and then he lies down for a while.
í (_) klötiu-gẽ jekepa í jẽk mõ-gẽ-wã panẽ
Next, outside the house there were others, and one of them came in and gave something to all of them, except him.
Jeska e-gla siga-wa tsõ jũ shebega dögẽu e-gla Jẽk kö-gẽ-wã jẽk pakkö-gẽ-wã í (m) jũ jãrga Je të jirö mẽ-gẽ ĩã kable ĩã í mẽ-nã ta jie ka ĩã í mẽnẽ

spanGrp.span: he walked towards him and asked him why he didn’t give him something, but the other one ignored him.
Je kueinga je e-gla mẽnẽu töinga í mẽnẽu í shö í ĩã-nã jirö kueinga ka jie ĩã mẽnẽ e-gla ka í kögane
So he went back to his place and sat in front of the others.
kueinga í jẽk betẽũ jẽk ká-wã-nẽ etaba_gicha siga-wa wömĩ
They were all eating but did not give him a share;
siga-wa tsõ jirö ñõ wömĩ ta (m) jie ka ĩã mẽnẽ
and that made him very sad;
je të í jẽr iáwa-wã tã'ĩ
jewa mẽnẽu-mĩ-nẽ esteee… etaba_gicha jũ shebega
Many of them were eating and so he became sad.
Nẽranã siga-wa tsõ tã'ĩ siga-wa tsõ tã'ĩ jirö ñõ ta jie kai jie/ í (m) jẽr iawã'-wã
He then walked towards one who was reading a book, but that one ran away from him.
í mẽnẽu-mĩ-nẽ e-gla dul jirö anẽtsö wömĩ nẽ ñe je tönã'u-mĩ í yiga
Actually, he went to fetch something to give to him;
(_) Je je tönã'u-mĩ í yiga mẽnẽu-mĩ-nẽ jirö tsõ Je të je të jirö mã' ĩã
they gave him something and he ate it.
ee… je je je kable jirö jirö mẽ-nã' ĩã je ñã'-wã-ite
there were many of them working, so he walked in amid them.
siga-wa tsõ shkablö je shanã í jẽk pakká-wã-nẽ
There seem to be people fighting;
Pe tsõ juela rö ñã kbö bi
there is something there and he walked in the middle of it.
jirö tsõ bi je shanã í jẽk pakká-wã
The others did not give him anything and keep things away from him.
í siga-wa ka jirö mẽnẽ ĩã í siga-wa të jirö kẽwẽ-gẽ í yiga
That makes him sad again, and then he got angry and threw the rifle away.
Je të tã'ĩ jie jẽr ia-nẽ-wẽ-gẽ je kueinganã jie jie jie ulunã'-wã tã'ĩ í mõglö báu-mĩ-ite
He then walked towards a man who was reading a book, who then stood up and walked away from him.
je kueinga jie të… (_) í jẽk… jẽk kã'-wã mãĩ (_) ñãra/ e-gla kajki e-gla pekaga kajki juyukwo anẽtsõ wömĩ jie jẽk döá-wã Je mẽnẽu-mĩ í yiga
He thus sat there for a while.
jie jẽk kã'-wã panẽ je inga
During all that he sat down and got very sad.
Je je wögataranã í… í mẽnẽu í mẽnẽu jẽk kã'-wã Kepa í jẽr ianã'k-ka
Later on, a man came and gave him something, which he ate.
kepa benaparanã e-gla pekaga dajũ wã jirö shkö ĩã je ñã'-wã-ite
The others were looking and laughing at him; that made him angry and so he walked away from them
Siga-wa tsõ siwã' inga wö kö-gẽ í sũã' je të jeñẽtse-gẽ je të tã'ĩ jie uluwã'-wã Í tunã'u-mĩ í yiga
He then came back again; people were working.
Tögapa í deu-nẽ-ra-nã ele… etaba_gicha pe tsõ ĩã shkablö pe tsõ shkablö
Why would they not give him anaything?
¿Ta jie ka ĩã jirö mẽ-l ta jirö kueinga í
He got angry and went back to sleep.
Jie uluwã'-wã tã'ĩ í mẽnẽu jẽk mã'mĩ köpö-nẽ etaba_gicha nẽ
He sat down to eat; he saw that the others were laughing at him.
Jewanã í jẽk ká-wã yökö-nẽ-ra-nã sũã'-ite-ra siga-wa të jeñẽtse-gẽ
The others were eating and laughing at him.
Siga-wa ñerö/ siga-wa tsõ yökö të jie jeñẽtse-gẽ-nẽ
Then he was eating, why don’t they give him anything?
Jekepa í kajki yökö ¿Jie ka ĩã jirö mẽ-l kueinga
So he walked away and got very angry.
Jewa jie mẽnẽu-mĩ-nẽ jie mẽnẽu je ulunã'-wã tã'ĩ
He opened something; they gave him something he was eating something;
jie të jirö köyegẽ jirö mẽ-nã' ĩã köyáu-mĩ je ñõ kajki-ra-nã
he got mad and threw it up in the air and it fell on a man’s face;
je jie ulunã'-wã të je kueinga je jũã' siwã' inga janã-ka pekaga wö inga
the man threw it back to him.
Je pekaga të jũã'u-te-nẽ jie inga nẽ
